      <h3>Small enough to carry. <span class="it">Large enough to live inside</span> for an afternoon.</h3>

      <div class="body">
        <p><span class="dropcap">A</span> fairy village is small enough to carry and large enough to live inside for an afternoon. Felt homes with petal roofs and embroidered doors, little wooden folk in stitched hoods, a round wool mat with a carrot garden growing through it. Together they make one world a young child sets up, rearranges, and returns to. There are no batteries. There are no instructions. There is no right way to play. The tending is the play.</p>
        <p>Every house here is needle-felted by hand in Nepal. The wool keeps a child's body heat the way a real cottage does. The petal roofs curl a little differently on every piece. That difference is the work.</p>
      </div>

